msContents.summary: Copy of al-Bayḍāwī's commentary on the Qurʼān with a partial table of contents added at the beginning.

author.name: Free Library of Philadelphia. Rare Book Department. John Frederick Lewis Collection of Oriental Manuscripts

supportDesc.extent: i, 369, ii leaves : 270 x 177 (201 x 126) mm, bound to 270 x 177 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Foliated in Hindu-Arabic numerals in ink with some misnumbering (1-79, 81-83, 85-369) upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 33 long lines; frame ruled with a misṭarah. Some marginal headers; many marginal notes.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink with titles in thuluth in red ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Illuminated frontispiece and title page in three registers with the main space colored blue with corner pieces in gold and colors and a central shamsah containing the subtitle and author's name in gold; the title appears in gold and white in a rectangle above with a third register above that with decoration in polychrome and gold (f. 1r); polychrome and gold headpiece and circular vignette (f. 1v); verses of the Qurʼān and sūrah titles in red.

binding.p: Bound in brown leather over pasteboard with gold-tooled central mandorla, two pendants on the vertical axis and cornerpieces; inside covers of brown leather with a filigree patterned central mandorla in black and gold over green textile; gold-tooled corners and frame.

origin.p: Item is undated, possibly 14th or early 15th century based on the style of decoration and the paper.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by John Frederick Lewis.
